        "cooked": "<p>Greetings Signal users,</p>\n<p>I have a slightly unique little problem on my hands, as follows:<br>\nSignal kindly places a notification icon on my lock screen when I have unread messages. This is usually the standard Signal icon, which is fine.</p>\n<p>However, I have one particular contact which I would like to distinguish from all others (this contact sends me alerts). I would like to be able to look at my lock screen and be able to tell if I have unread messages from this special contact, or just general messages.<br>\nWhen playing around with custom notification settings, I turned on ‘Set this chat as not a conversation’. After doing this, new messages from this contact were shown on the lock screen as a small circle with an ‘S’ inside. I thought this was a placeholder for the profile picture / avatar, since this sender did not have an avatar set, and the name began with ‘S’. So far so good.</p>\n<p>However, after setting an avatar on the <em>sending</em> Signal account, the icon used on the lock screen is the standard Signal icon. Not only is this not what I want, it also confuses me, as the behaviour has changed…</p>\n<p>Apologies for the long post, would appreciate any advice, explanations or suggestions. <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/smiley.png?v=12\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
